  <article> 
    <title> the poldek </title>
    <author>  </author>
    <date> </date>
    
    <sect> Introduction
    <p>
    The poldek is designed to automate the verify, install and upgrade 
    of rpm packages. It can be used in batch or interactive mode. 
    It was inspired by <em>apt_get</em> from Debian's APT, the interactive mode 
    was inspired by shell mode of Perl CPAN module <em>($ perl -MCPAN -e shell)</em>.
    
    For more information see 
	<url url="poldek.html" name="man page">, 
    see also PLD admin manual 
    <url url="http://team.pld.org.pl/~klakier/doc/pld-admin-manual/en/index.html#id129972" 
         name="subsection about poldek">
    </sect> 

    <sect> Availability
    <p>
    The program is free software (GPL).
    It is not yet well tested so consider it "beta" software. 

    <itemize> 

    <item> Homepage 

      <url url="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/" 
           name="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/"> 
    </item>
    

    <item> Source tarballs and rpm source packages
      <itemize>
      <item> <url url="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/download/poldek-@VERSION@.tar.gz" 
                  name="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/download/poldek-@VERSION@.tar.gz"> 

      <item> <url url="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/download/poldek-@VERSION@-1.src.rpm" 
                  name="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/download/poldek-@VERSION@-1.src.rpm">  
      </itemize>
    </item>

    <item> Binary rpm packages for several architectures can be downloaded from
                 <url url="http://www.pld.org.pl/" name="PLD"> ftp site 
         <url url="ftp://ftp.pld.org.pl/" name="ftp://ftp.pld.org.pl/"> (directory
         PLD-1.0/<em>ARCH</em>/PLD/RPMS/)
        
    </item>

    <item> Anonymous CVS
    <p>
      Getting the module (password: "cvs"): 
      <tscreen><verb>
      cvs -d :pserver:cvs@anoncvs.pld.org.pl:/cvsroot login
      cvs -d :pserver:cvs@anoncvs.pld.org.pl:/cvsroot get installer/poldek
      </verb></tscreen>            
      Particular files may be accessed via 
	<url url="http://cvs.pld.org.pl/installer/poldek/" name="CVSWeb">

    </item>
    </itemize>
    </sect>
    
    <sect> Build
    <p>
    Program depends on following packages/libraries: bzip2, curl, db3, glibc, ncurses, openssl, 
     pcre, popt, readline, rpm, zlib and trurlib. <p>
    The last one, <em>trurlib</em> is small C library with some useful data structures and routines, 
    it can be downloaded from following URLs:
     <itemize>
      <item> source 
         <url url="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/download/trurlib-@TRURLIB_VERSION@.tar.gz" 
              name="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/download/trurlib-@TRURLIB_VERSION@.tar.gz">

      <item> source rpm package 
         <url url="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/download/trurlib-@TRURLIB_VERSION@-1.src.rpm" 
             name="http://team.pld.org.pl/~mis/poldek/download/trurlib-@TRURLIB_VERSION@-1.src.rpm"> 

      <item> binary rpm packages <url url="ftp://ftp.pld.org.pl/" 
             name="ftp://team.pld.org.pl/"> (directory PLD-1.0/<em>ARCH</em>/PLD/RPMS/)
      </itemize>
    </sect>
       
    
